title: For Sale:  Savage 10 FCP-SR
postcontent: This is a hard to find Savage 10 FCP-SR in digital camo (the Savage Manufacturer part number is 19480).  It's chambered in .308/7.62 NATO.  This isn't the new model FCP-SR that's on every shelf in every box store.  Guys who shoot long range know this is a vastly superior build compared to the new model.  I configured this rifle for a long range class I took in Virginia that was taught by Dan Newbury. The rifle features a 24 inch heavy fluted barrel with a muzzle break, a one piece picitinny rail, digital camo AccuStock, AccuTrigger, and an all steel construction 10 round detachable box magazine by Accurate Mag Company.  In addition to that, I have a 6-18 Vortex Crossfire II scope with a level attached, a cheek riser, and an imitation Harris bipod.  I zeroed the rifle at a hundred yards last August, cleaned it, oiled it, and put it away.  The only adjustment I never made to it is on the magazine feed lip.  I never bothered to buy the adjustment tool because I feed the ammo by hand one round at a time when I shoot long range.  The mag feed lip probably needs to be opened up about 3 thousandths or so to get the cartridges to feed more smoothly.  The adjustment tool costs about 25 bucks.If you have any questions, feel free to ask.  If the ad is up, the rifle is still for sale.  1000 dollars gets everything I listed in the ad.  900 gets you everything but the optic.  Not looking for trades at this time.  And thanks for your interest.
